21
00:00:59.182 --> 00:01:00.449
Honey. if you grab the fishing gear.

22
00:01:00.484 --> 00:01:02.618
I'll go rent the boat.

23
00:01:05.020 --> 00:01:07.188
Hey. have fun.

24
00:01:07.223 --> 00:01:08.990
Good luck with the fishing.
Yeah.

25
00:01:09.024 --> 00:01:10.525
Remember to put on sunscreen.

26
00:01:10.559 --> 00:01:12.760
Okay.

27
00:01:20.202 --> 00:01:22.470
You gonna take pictures all afternoon?

28
00:01:22.505 --> 00:01:24.005
Got to share the fun. honey.

29
00:01:24.039 --> 00:01:26.241
Besides. you look cute in that life jacket.

30
00:01:28.310 --> 00:01:30.278
Ooh!

31
00:01:32.014 --> 00:01:35.150
I'm so excited! Bye!

32
00:01:35.184 --> 00:01:37.519
I was only in the restaurant
for about five minutes.

33
00:01:37.553 --> 00:01:40.221
- Juliette did this?
- No. Eve.

34
00:01:40.256 --> 00:01:41.422
Who the hell is Eve?

35
00:01:41.457 --> 00:01:42.390
She used to be Juliette.

36
00:01:42.424 --> 00:01:43.725
Used to be?

37
00:01:43.759 --> 00:01:45.293
She's definitely not the woman I knew.

38
00:01:45.327 --> 00:01:46.528
This was a planned hit.

39
00:01:46.562 --> 00:01:47.896
Turns out. I was her backup.

40
00:01:47.930 --> 00:01:49.164
- And you didn't know this?
- No.

41
00:01:49.198 --> 00:01:51.366
It was a test. I found that out later.

42
00:01:51.400 --> 00:01:53.501
- A test of what?
- To see if I could survive.

43
00:01:53.536 --> 00:01:55.203
Or if I'd protect her.

44
00:01:55.237 --> 00:01:57.906
You survived and she's
alive. so I guess you passed.

45
00:01:57.940 --> 00:01:59.107
I hope she thanked you.

46
00:01:59.141 --> 00:02:00.708
She didn't stick around.

47
00:02:00.743 --> 00:02:02.377
When I got out. she was gone.

48
00:02:02.411 --> 00:02:04.045
We know who her target was?

49
00:02:04.079 --> 00:02:05.213
The guy in the suit.

50
00:02:05.247 --> 00:02:06.848
Haven't been able to ID him yet

51
00:02:06.882 --> 00:02:09.384
or his bodyguards... they
weren't carrying identification.

52
00:02:09.418 --> 00:02:11.252
All I know is his name was Samuel Rankin.

53
00:02:11.287 --> 00:02:13.254
He was an organizer for Black Claw.

54
00:02:13.289 --> 00:02:15.123
If he didn't have ID.
how do you know all this?

55
00:02:15.157 --> 00:02:17.025
The guy Eve works for. he told me.

56
00:02:17.059 --> 00:02:19.294
His name's Meisner.

57
00:02:19.328 --> 00:02:20.562
Meisner?

58
00:02:20.596 --> 00:02:22.230
- You know him?
- Yeah. I know him.

59
00:02:22.264 --> 00:02:24.232
He's an independent agent
working out of Europe.

60
00:02:24.266 --> 00:02:26.000
He was working with the Resistance.

61
00:02:26.035 --> 00:02:27.202
Well. he's here now.

62
00:02:27.236 --> 00:02:28.970
And he's running Eve and Trubel.

63
00:02:29.004 --> 00:02:30.171
and he was working with Chavez.

64
00:02:30.206 --> 00:02:31.539
Chavez?

65
00:02:31.574 --> 00:02:32.874
So Meisner's a part of this group?

66
00:02:32.908 --> 00:02:35.777
He's in charge now.

67
00:02:36.656 --> 00:02:38.524
So how do we explain Rankin's death?

68
00:02:38.559 --> 00:02:39.960
Well. his bodyguards
were closest to him.

69
00:02:39.994 --> 00:02:41.227
so my feeling is we blame them.

70
00:02:41.262 --> 00:02:42.595
If you're gonna lay
it on the bodyguards.

71
00:02:42.630 --> 00:02:43.663
you better find out who they are.

72
00:02:43.698 --> 00:02:44.898
So
Juliette...

73
00:02:44.932 --> 00:02:47.133
I mean Eve. she's not tied to this at all?

74
00:02:47.168 --> 00:02:48.501
No.

75
00:02:48.536 --> 00:02:50.303
She never touched them.
Never even came close.

76
00:02:50.338 --> 00:02:51.404
Looks like they
planned this pretty well.

77
00:02:51.439 --> 00:02:52.572
Do we know why Rankin was here?

78
00:02:52.606 --> 00:02:54.174
Not yet.

79
00:02:54.208 --> 00:02:57.277
All right. make this
report as logical as possible.

80
00:02:57.311 --> 00:03:00.180
At least your suspects can't
object to a murder charge.

81
00:03:01.749 --> 00:03:04.451
Don't you think he should
have called us by now?

82
00:03:04.485 --> 00:03:05.852
Who?

83
00:03:05.886 --> 00:03:07.053
Nick.

84
00:03:07.088 --> 00:03:12.325
Oh. you mean after
the Juliette... "reunion"?

85
00:03:12.360 --> 00:03:13.893
Maybe it didn't go so well?

86
00:03:13.928 --> 00:03:17.197
I'm sure it wasn't without drama.

87
00:03:17.231 --> 00:03:19.633
Maybe we should call him.

88
00:03:19.667 --> 00:03:21.334
You should see this.

89
00:03:21.369 --> 00:03:24.771
What?

90
00:03:24.805 --> 00:03:27.741
Postmarked Seattle. just
like the other one you got.

91
00:03:28.586 --> 00:03:29.953
God. now what?

92
00:03:29.987 --> 00:03:32.322
Look. I really think
we got to deal with this.

93
00:03:32.356 --> 00:03:35.792
I mean. if you want me to
handle it. I'm happy to.

94
00:03:35.827 --> 00:03:37.561
Let's do it together.

95
00:03:37.595 --> 00:03:45.702
♪ ♪

96
00:03:45.736 --> 00:03:48.972
"Dear R. I thought you might write me back

97
00:03:49.006 --> 00:03:51.508
"after I told you about Carlos dying.

98
00:03:51.542 --> 00:03:54.377
"Maybe you don't want to hear from me.

99
00:03:54.412 --> 00:03:56.546
"But I don't know what you think about

100
00:03:56.581 --> 00:03:58.749
"what we used to have together.

101
00:03:58.783 --> 00:04:00.417
I'm thinking about
coming to Portland..."

102
00:04:00.451 --> 00:04:01.952
My God. I don't want to deal with this!

103
00:04:01.986 --> 00:04:03.520
Hang on a second.

104
00:04:03.554 --> 00:04:06.757
This guy is obviously
contacting you for a reason.

105
00:04:06.791 --> 00:04:08.692
Don't you think we got to figure out why?

106
00:04:08.726 --> 00:04:10.627
I mean. he just said he's
thinking of coming to Portland.

107
00:04:10.660 --> 00:04:12.294
What does this guy want from you?

108
00:04:12.329 --> 00:04:13.863
After all this time?

109
00:04:13.897 --> 00:04:15.664
I don't know.

110
00:04:15.699 --> 00:04:18.801
He thinks we had a relationship.

111
00:04:18.835 --> 00:04:21.971
We didn't.

112
00:04:22.005 --> 00:04:23.506
Except the drug part.

113
00:04:23.540 --> 00:04:24.874
This is.
you know...

114
00:04:24.908 --> 00:04:28.511
This is just... so stupid.

115
00:04:28.545 --> 00:04:30.713
♪ ♪

116
00:04:35.584 --> 00:04:37.285
Honey. I got one!

117
00:04:37.319 --> 00:04:38.286
Oh.

118
00:04:39.688 --> 00:04:41.222
That's definitely going on Facebook.

119
00:04:41.257 --> 00:04:42.223
Oh. please. Elizabeth.

120
00:04:42.258 --> 00:04:43.725
No.
Just kidding.

121
00:04:43.759 --> 00:04:45.760
It's going on Instagram.

122
00:04:47.696 --> 00:04:49.731
Allan? What's that?

123
00:04:49.765 --> 00:04:51.833
- What?
- That.

124
00:04:51.867 --> 00:04:54.402
Something's moving underwater.

125
00:04:54.436 --> 00:04:56.170
It's probably just a catfish.

126
00:04:56.205 --> 00:04:58.206
Pretty big for a catfish.

127
00:05:01.343 --> 00:05:02.544
Oh. my God.

128
00:05:02.578 --> 00:05:04.912
It's swimming around us.

129
00:05:04.947 --> 00:05:06.047
What the hell is it?

130
00:05:06.081 --> 00:05:07.849
Uh...

131
00:05:10.119 --> 00:05:12.353
♪ ♪

132
00:05:12.388 --> 00:05:13.955
Oh. my God. shoot a picture of that.

133
00:05:13.989 --> 00:05:16.157
Uh...

134
00:05:17.426 --> 00:05:19.093
Oh. my God!

135
00:05:19.128 --> 00:05:21.696
♪ ♪

136
00:05:21.730 --> 00:05:23.364
Did you see what it was?
No.

137
00:05:23.399 --> 00:05:24.732
I think it's time to go back to shore.

138
00:05:24.767 --> 00:05:26.401
Yeah.

139
00:05:26.435 --> 00:05:28.002
Allan?

140
00:05:28.037 --> 00:05:29.103
It's coming back!

141
00:05:29.138 --> 00:05:33.308
♪ ♪

142
00:05:33.342 --> 00:05:35.310
Allan? Allan! Oh. my God!

143
00:05:35.344 --> 00:05:37.278
It's coming out of the water!

144
00:05:41.317 --> 00:05:48.790
♪ ♪

145
00:05:50.961 --> 00:05:53.763
Whoa! Whoa! Ah!

146
00:05:53.797 --> 00:05:55.932
Allan?

147
00:05:55.966 --> 00:05:57.734
Honey. it's right behind you!

148
00:05:57.768 --> 00:05:59.335
Help me!

149
00:05:59.369 --> 00:06:00.803
Allan!

150
00:06:00.838 --> 00:06:03.573
Oh.
my... Allan.

151
00:06:03.607 --> 00:06:05.475
Allan!

152
00:06:05.509 --> 00:06:08.745
Allan. Allan. Allan!

153
00:06:11.448 --> 00:06:14.684
Allan! Allan!

154
00:06:14.718 --> 00:06:16.219
<i>Allan!</i>

155
00:06:20.724 --> 00:06:26.696
♪ ♪

156
00:06:26.718 --> 00:06:29.005
