157
00:06:29.003 --> 00:06:32.038
<i>Allan!</i>

158
00:06:32.072 --> 00:06:35.238
<i>Allan! Oh. my God!</i>

159
00:06:35.116 --> 00:06:36.616
Oh. no. no. no. no. no.

160
00:06:36.650 --> 00:06:39.752
<i>Help! Allan!</i>

161
00:06:39.787 --> 00:06:42.188
<i>Help me! Allan!</i>

162
00:06:52.433 --> 00:06:53.500
What the hell did you do?

163
00:06:53.534 --> 00:06:55.502
Guy started shooting at me.

164
00:06:55.536 --> 00:06:56.970
so I had to take care of him.

165
00:06:57.004 --> 00:06:58.538
What do you mean. "take care of him"?

166
00:06:58.572 --> 00:06:59.806
I had to put him down.

167
00:06:59.840 --> 00:07:01.608
- You killed somebody?
- He had a gun!

168
00:07:01.642 --> 00:07:03.510
He was trying to kill me!

169
00:07:03.544 --> 00:07:05.845
<i>Allan!</i>

170
00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:07.247
What was I supposed to do?

171
00:07:07.281 --> 00:07:08.782
It was sort of like self-defense.

172
00:07:08.816 --> 00:07:10.550
Oh. my God. Wayne.

173
00:07:10.584 --> 00:07:11.551
Where's my money?

174
00:07:11.585 --> 00:07:13.953
<i>Allan!</i>

175
00:07:13.988 --> 00:07:15.355
We'll sort this out later.

176
00:07:15.389 --> 00:07:17.056
<i>Allan!</i>

177
00:07:17.091 --> 00:07:18.892
She's making a hell of a racket.

178
00:07:18.926 --> 00:07:21.695
<i>Lucky I didn't kill her too.</i>

179
00:07:21.729 --> 00:07:23.430
Get out of here.

180
00:07:23.464 --> 00:07:25.198
<i>Allan!</i>

181
00:07:25.232 --> 00:07:26.232
This wasn't supposed to happen.

182
00:07:26.267 --> 00:07:27.567
That guy is an idiot!

183
00:07:27.601 --> 00:07:28.601
- Calm down.
- Calm down?

184
00:07:28.636 --> 00:07:29.803
What are we gonna do now?

185
00:07:29.837 --> 00:07:31.404
<i>- Shut up.
- No!</i>

186
00:07:31.439 --> 00:07:33.139
They're never gonna
connect us to anything.

187
00:07:33.174 --> 00:07:34.908
She'll never be able
to identify him anyway.

188
00:07:34.942 --> 00:07:36.209
He was woged the whole time.

189
00:07:36.243 --> 00:07:37.277
<i>Oh. my God!</i>

190
00:07:37.311 --> 00:07:38.445
So what do we do?

191
00:07:38.479 --> 00:07:41.614
<i>- Help me!
- Call 911.</i>

192
00:07:42.254 --> 00:07:44.088
<i>I got nothing on any of the victims.</i>

193
00:07:44.122 --> 00:07:46.223
The fingerprints don't
match anything we got.

194
00:07:46.258 --> 00:07:48.659
They located a rental car
that we matched to the victims.

195
00:07:48.694 --> 00:07:51.495
but the ID used to rent the car was stolen.

196
00:07:51.530 --> 00:07:53.064
So was the credit card.

197
00:07:53.098 --> 00:07:54.098
What do we do next?

198
00:07:54.132 --> 00:07:55.199
Always dental records.

199
00:07:55.233 --> 00:07:57.001
Hey. Nick.

200
00:07:57.035 --> 00:07:59.203
I've been thinking about what
happened to you last night.

201
00:07:59.237 --> 00:08:02.506
Hey. Hank. Hey. Wu.

202
00:08:02.541 --> 00:08:04.275
Are you pissed?

203
00:08:04.309 --> 00:08:05.509
I'd be pissed.

204
00:08:05.544 --> 00:08:07.945
I am pissed. They should've told you.

205
00:08:07.980 --> 00:08:11.015
It would've been nice
to know who I had to kill.

206
00:08:11.049 --> 00:08:14.719
That would be Samuel
Rankin's two Schakal bodyguards.

207
00:08:14.753 --> 00:08:16.220
Sig Ganz...

208
00:08:19.329 --> 00:08:19.791
Czech national. 32.

209
00:08:19.825 --> 00:08:22.747
Not that he was using that name.

210
00:08:22.794 --> 00:08:26.363
Born in Tuchomence. recruited
by Black Claw three years ago.

211
00:08:26.397 --> 00:08:27.998
And Otto Gruenwaldt...

212
00:08:29.601 --> 00:08:32.536
36. born in Woltersdorf. East Germany.

213
00:08:33.131 --> 00:08:34.598
His father was Stasi.

214
00:08:34.633 --> 00:08:36.700
Black Claw enforcer.
recruited four years ago.

215
00:08:36.735 --> 00:08:38.369
You know anything about Samuel Rankin?

216
00:08:38.403 --> 00:08:40.538
Yeah.

217
00:08:40.572 --> 00:08:42.306
Real name Rolf Kleinager.

218
00:08:43.642 --> 00:08:46.243
One of the founders of Black Claw.

219
00:08:46.278 --> 00:08:48.813
I mean. we're pretty sure
he met with Alva Zajic

220
00:08:48.847 --> 00:08:50.514
and Arnaud Dubois ten years ago

221
00:08:50.549 --> 00:08:53.451
at the thermal baths
outside of Bad Zurzach.

222
00:08:53.485 --> 00:08:56.086
It's a small Swiss town on
the edge of the Black Forest.

223
00:08:56.121 --> 00:08:58.255
Kleinager was a big kill for us.

224
00:08:58.290 --> 00:09:00.224
Oh. and. um. Meisner called.

225
00:09:00.258 --> 00:09:01.425
That's why I'm here.

226
00:09:01.460 --> 00:09:02.660
He wants to talk to you.

227
00:09:02.694 --> 00:09:04.495
- When?
- Now.

228
00:09:04.529 --> 00:09:12.436
♪ ♪

229
00:09:22.949 --> 00:09:24.483
Obviously. we're not alone.

230
00:09:24.517 --> 00:09:26.284
<i>No.</i>

231
00:09:26.319 --> 00:09:28.487
You're not.

232
00:09:31.023 --> 00:09:32.690
There was no other way.

233
00:09:32.724 --> 00:09:33.824
But you proved yourself.

234
00:09:33.859 --> 00:09:35.493
To who?

235
00:09:35.527 --> 00:09:36.727
Eve.

236
00:09:36.762 --> 00:09:44.702
♪ ♪

237
00:10:28.828 --> 00:10:31.363
This is my room.

238
00:10:31.397 --> 00:10:35.166
This is where they put you.

239
00:10:35.201 --> 00:10:37.635
This is where they put all of us.

240
00:10:37.670 --> 00:10:39.571
Who is "they"?

241
00:10:39.605 --> 00:10:42.207
Branch of the Federal Government.

242
00:10:42.241 --> 00:10:43.508
Don't try to find it.

243
00:10:43.542 --> 00:10:45.844
It doesn't exist.

244
00:10:45.878 --> 00:10:48.313
So I suppose I've
never seen any of this.

245
00:10:50.549 --> 00:10:51.716
Where's Eve?

246
00:10:51.751 --> 00:10:56.388
♪ ♪

247
00:10:56.422 --> 00:10:57.956
I'll be here. Nick.

248
00:10:57.990 --> 00:11:01.292
♪ ♪

249
00:11:06.532 --> 00:11:09.300
So Renard told me you
worked for the Resistance.

250
00:11:09.335 --> 00:11:11.369
I did.

251
00:11:11.404 --> 00:11:12.804
But this is much bigger than that.

252
00:11:12.838 --> 00:11:14.506
How high up does this go?

253
00:11:14.540 --> 00:11:16.074
I don't know.

254
00:11:16.108 --> 00:11:18.076
But as you can tell.
we're not without funding.

255
00:11:18.110 --> 00:11:19.944
And don't ask me where
that comes from either.

256
00:11:19.979 --> 00:11:21.446
'Cause I don't know.

257
00:11:21.480 --> 00:11:23.014
She's inside.

258
00:11:23.049 --> 00:11:26.051
I'll give you a few minutes.

259
00:11:26.085 --> 00:11:27.252
<i>Enter.</i>

260
00:11:27.286 --> 00:11:32.390
♪ ♪

261
00:11:35.361 --> 00:11:43.301
♪ ♪

262
00:11:48.146 --> 00:11:51.148
You wanted me to prove myself?

263
00:11:53.184 --> 00:11:56.753
You did.

264
00:11:56.788 --> 00:11:59.156
You should've told me.

265
00:11:59.190 --> 00:12:01.658
We had to know how you would react.

266
00:12:01.692 --> 00:12:03.193
If you let your emotions get in the way.

267
00:12:03.227 --> 00:12:06.229
you'd be no good to us.

268
00:12:10.868 --> 00:12:13.136
You really believe in all of this.

269
00:12:13.171 --> 00:12:16.239
Not at first. I didn't
believe in anything.

270
00:12:16.274 --> 00:12:18.275
What about now?

271
00:12:20.945 --> 00:12:22.913
I found a reason to live.

272
00:12:22.947 --> 00:12:30.887
♪ ♪

273
00:12:33.057 --> 00:12:35.926
Do you feel remorse
for anything you've done?

274
00:12:35.960 --> 00:12:38.028
You mean what she did.

275
00:12:38.062 --> 00:12:40.697
<i>What you did.</i>

276
00:12:41.087 --> 00:12:45.757
You still think you're
talking to Juliette.

277
00:12:45.791 --> 00:12:47.225
I don't know who I'm talking to.

278
00:12:47.259 --> 00:12:50.795
Yes. you do. You just won't accept it.

279
00:12:50.830 --> 00:12:53.164
Maybe I can't.

280
00:12:53.199 --> 00:12:54.432
If we're gonna work together.

281
00:12:54.467 --> 00:12:56.367
you have to stop living in your past.

282
00:12:56.402 --> 00:12:57.769
What do you mean. "work together"?

283
00:12:57.803 --> 00:12:59.771
You're here for a reason.

284
00:12:59.805 --> 00:13:03.341
♪ ♪

285
00:13:03.375 --> 00:13:04.676
My only regret is that you didn't

286
00:13:04.710 --> 00:13:08.747
have a chance to bury Juliette.

287
00:13:09.960 --> 00:13:12.194
There's more for you to see.

288
00:13:12.229 --> 00:13:20.303
♪ ♪

289
00:13:23.307 --> 00:13:28.010
♪ ♪

290
00:13:28.045 --> 00:13:30.212
This is one of HW's command centers.

291
00:13:30.247 --> 00:13:31.213
There are more?

292
00:13:31.248 --> 00:13:32.448
Oh. yeah. This is a war.

293
00:13:32.482 --> 00:13:33.849
It's happening all over the world.

294
00:13:33.884 --> 00:13:35.918
And we're fighting it.

295
00:13:35.953 --> 00:13:39.922
Take a look at this.

296
00:13:39.957 --> 00:13:41.924
The hot spots are Wesen uprisings:

297
00:13:41.959 --> 00:13:44.126
Brazil. Northern Ireland. Turkey. Syria.

298
00:13:44.161 --> 00:13:46.062
Yemen. Pakistan. Ukraine.

299
00:13:46.096 --> 00:13:48.097
- That's all Wesen related?
- All of it.

300
00:13:48.131 --> 00:13:50.032
There are people
displaced all over the world

301
00:13:50.067 --> 00:13:51.567
because of what they're doing.

302
00:13:51.602 --> 00:13:54.303
No one understands the
real reason behind any of it.

303
00:13:54.338 --> 00:13:55.638
Which is what?

304
00:13:55.672 --> 00:13:58.641
A world run by Wesen.

305
00:13:58.675 --> 00:14:02.011
Hitler tried once. now
Black Claw is trying again.

306
00:14:02.045 --> 00:14:09.018
♪ ♪

307
00:14:09.052 --> 00:14:10.953
Let me show you something.

308
00:14:10.988 --> 00:14:16.525
♪ ♪

309
00:14:16.560 --> 00:14:20.062
- What is this?
- It's our graveyard.

310
00:14:20.097 --> 00:14:21.697
Chavez is here.

311
00:14:21.732 --> 00:14:23.900
The ones you were supposed
to meet are here too.

312
00:14:23.934 --> 00:14:25.668
So you cleaned it up.

313
00:14:25.702 --> 00:14:28.437
We had to.

314
00:14:28.472 --> 00:14:31.274
Why bring me here?

315
00:14:31.308 --> 00:14:33.342
Three days after we took Juliette.

316
00:14:33.377 --> 00:14:36.379
we found where Kenneth had
dumped your mother's body.

317
00:14:36.413 --> 00:14:39.482
We recovered it and what
we took from your house

318
00:14:39.516 --> 00:14:42.652
and... and buried her here.

319
00:14:42.686 --> 00:14:46.022
♪ ♪

320
00:14:46.056 --> 00:14:48.558
Just in case you don't believe me.

321
00:14:51.595 --> 00:14:59.235
♪ ♪

322
00:14:59.269 --> 00:15:01.537
We want your help.

323
00:15:01.572 --> 00:15:04.040
We need it for what's coming.

324
00:15:04.074 --> 00:15:12.114
♪ ♪

325
00:15:35.239 --> 00:15:37.073
Is he okay?

326
00:15:37.107 --> 00:15:40.476
♪ ♪

327
00:15:40.510 --> 00:15:42.478
He will be.

328
00:15:42.512 --> 00:15:50.553
♪ ♪

329
00:15:56.228 --> 00:15:58.696
It was swimming all around us.

330
00:15:58.730 --> 00:16:00.698
We were gonna go back to shore.

331
00:16:00.733 --> 00:16:01.999
What stopped you?

332
00:16:02.034 --> 00:16:04.302
It hit our boat.

333
00:16:04.336 --> 00:16:05.603
Dragged my husband under.

334
00:16:05.637 --> 00:16:07.672
Something knocked him into the water?

335
00:16:07.706 --> 00:16:09.006
You don't understand.

336
00:16:09.041 --> 00:16:10.942
It attacked us.

337
00:16:10.976 --> 00:16:12.410
What attacked you?

338
00:16:12.444 --> 00:16:13.845
This.

339
00:16:15.881 --> 00:16:17.682
This is getting so out of control.

340
00:16:17.716 --> 00:16:19.417
- Calm down.
- It's your fault.

341
00:16:19.451 --> 00:16:20.918
You're overreacting.

342
00:16:20.953 --> 00:16:23.087
A man is dead. Wayne.
and we're responsible.

343
00:16:23.122 --> 00:16:24.856
We're not responsible. Logan is!

344
00:16:24.890 --> 00:16:27.225
Yeah. we hired Logan to scare people.

345
00:16:27.259 --> 00:16:29.360
not to kill them.

346
00:16:29.394 --> 00:16:31.696
The whole thing backfired.

347
00:16:31.730 --> 00:16:34.031
You know what. we need to
close and get out of here.

348
00:16:35.267 --> 00:16:37.702
Be quiet.

349
00:16:37.736 --> 00:16:39.036
You guys rent the boats. right?

350
00:16:39.071 --> 00:16:40.571
- Sure do.
- Great.

351
00:16:40.606 --> 00:16:42.407
We need to get out on
that water right away.

352
00:16:42.441 --> 00:16:46.210
Just need you to fill out these forms.

353
00:16:46.245 --> 00:16:47.645
No problem.

354
00:16:47.679 --> 00:16:49.414
- You guys reporters?
- Yeah.

355
00:16:49.448 --> 00:16:52.049
Guess you guys have heard
of the Diamond Lake monster.

356
00:16:52.084 --> 00:16:53.584
Kind of a legend around these parts.

357
00:16:53.619 --> 00:16:55.319
Word is that it killed somebody.

358
00:16:55.354 --> 00:16:56.988
You here to cover it?

359
00:16:57.022 --> 00:16:58.456
If it bleeds. it leads.

360
00:16:58.490 --> 00:17:00.391
Not that I believe in
monsters. but whatever.

361
00:17:00.426 --> 00:17:02.126
Hey. how much for the cap?

362
00:17:02.161 --> 00:17:04.996
- Uh. it's $12.95
- 15 bucks.

363
00:17:05.030 --> 00:17:06.998
I'll take one of these shirts too.

364
00:17:07.032 --> 00:17:08.900
You know. wouldn't it be
great if it was a monster

365
00:17:08.934 --> 00:17:11.269
and not the usual homicidal maniac?

366
00:17:13.872 --> 00:17:17.408
Hey. Rebecca. you want one of these?

367
00:17:17.443 --> 00:17:18.676
Sure. why not?

368
00:17:18.710 --> 00:17:21.345
I'm a believer.

369
00:17:21.380 --> 00:17:24.081
I really hope we get a
chance to see this thing.

370
00:17:27.052 --> 00:17:28.920
You okay?

371
00:17:28.954 --> 00:17:30.555
I don't even know how to answer that.

372
00:17:30.589 --> 00:17:32.356
You talk to Meisner?

373
00:17:32.391 --> 00:17:34.358
- Yeah.
- So it's bad?

374
00:17:34.393 --> 00:17:35.760
We're at war.

375
00:17:35.794 --> 00:17:38.896
And nobody knows it.

376
00:17:38.931 --> 00:17:41.732
In my office. You need to see this.

377
00:17:43.202 --> 00:17:46.437
<i>- The Diamond Lake
Monster: fact or fiction?</i>

378
00:17:46.472 --> 00:17:48.639
<i>Early this morning.
Allan Eiger and his wife</i>

379
00:17:48.674 --> 00:17:50.208
<i>were out fishing on Diamond Lake</i>

380
00:17:50.242 --> 00:17:52.677
<i>when he was confronted
by that very question.</i>

381
00:17:52.711 --> 00:17:55.313
<i>The answer cost him his life.</i>

382
00:17:55.347 --> 00:17:57.315
<i>Some locals claim this gruesome attack</i>

383
00:17:57.349 --> 00:18:00.384
<i>is the work of the mysterious
Diamond Lake Monster.</i>

384
00:18:00.419 --> 00:18:03.254
<i>Could this be a local legend come to life?</i>

385
00:18:03.288 --> 00:18:05.790
<i>The victim's wife took
this startling image</i>

386
00:18:05.824 --> 00:18:07.825
<i>during the attack.</i>

387
00:18:07.860 --> 00:18:09.227
Are you kidding me?

388
00:18:09.261 --> 00:18:11.662
No. I got a call from Sheriff Parcell.

389
00:18:11.697 --> 00:18:14.932
He knows you've had luck with
some of these strange cases.

390
00:18:14.967 --> 00:18:16.401
He requested your help on this.

391
00:18:16.435 --> 00:18:18.336
Thinking this lake monster is Wesen?

392
00:18:18.370 --> 00:18:20.705
I don't believe in monsters
unless they're people.

393
00:18:20.739 --> 00:18:22.607
And this one is guilty of murder.

394
00:18:22.641 --> 00:18:23.608
We'll check it out.

395
00:18:23.642 --> 00:18:26.411
♪ ♪

396
00:18:26.445 --> 00:18:27.945
<i>This what we're looking for?</i>

397
00:18:27.980 --> 00:18:30.448
<i>This is what they're all looking for.</i>

398
00:18:30.482 --> 00:18:34.419
♪ ♪

399
00:18:34.453 --> 00:18:35.420
Thanks for coming.

400
00:18:35.454 --> 00:18:37.321
Oof. So. this
is a cluster...

401
00:18:37.356 --> 00:18:39.123
It is.

402
00:18:39.158 --> 00:18:41.559
I know you guys have dealt
with some pretty odd cases

403
00:18:41.593 --> 00:18:43.027
and I thought maybe you might be able

404
00:18:43.061 --> 00:18:44.262
to help us figure this one out.

405
00:18:44.296 --> 00:18:45.763
What do we know?

406
00:18:45.798 --> 00:18:47.565
Allan and Elizabeth
Eiger were on the lake

407
00:18:47.599 --> 00:18:49.567
when something attacked.

408
00:18:49.601 --> 00:18:51.769
Allan had a gun in his tackle box.

409
00:18:51.804 --> 00:18:54.705
he fired a few shots at it.
and it rammed their boat.

410
00:18:54.740 --> 00:18:56.574
He got knocked overboard. and this thing.

411
00:18:56.608 --> 00:18:58.710
whatever it was. pulled him under.

412
00:18:58.744 --> 00:18:59.777
ripped the hell out of him.

413
00:18:59.812 --> 00:19:00.778
Wife saw the whole thing.

414
00:19:00.813 --> 00:19:02.113
And she took the photo?

415
00:19:02.147 --> 00:19:03.781
Yeah. She's over there.

416
00:19:03.816 --> 00:19:05.083
Do you think it was a monster?

417
00:19:05.117 --> 00:19:06.584
I don't know what to think.

418
00:19:06.618 --> 00:19:08.786
This lake monster's just
a local big fish story

419
00:19:08.821 --> 00:19:11.656
like the Loch Ness Monster or Ogopogo.

420
00:19:11.690 --> 00:19:14.425
Somebody shot a blurry
photo back in the '60s.

421
00:19:14.460 --> 00:19:15.893
started the whole legend.

422
00:19:15.928 --> 00:19:17.996
Has this legend ever
attacked anybody before?

423
00:19:18.030 --> 00:19:19.263
I checked the records.

424
00:19:19.298 --> 00:19:20.798
There were a half dozen sightings

425
00:19:20.833 --> 00:19:23.334
over the last 40 years.
but nobody was ever hurt.

426
00:19:23.369 --> 00:19:25.336
Working theory is that
somebody dumped a pet gator

427
00:19:25.371 --> 00:19:27.138
that got too big.

428
00:19:27.172 --> 00:19:30.141
Fish and Game's out on the
lake looking for it with sonar.

429
00:19:30.175 --> 00:19:33.144
We'll talk to the victim's wife.

430
00:19:33.178 --> 00:19:34.812
Mrs. Eiger?

431
00:19:34.847 --> 00:19:36.914
I'm Detective Griffin.
this is Detective Burkhardt.

432
00:19:36.949 --> 00:19:38.316
We'd like to ask you a few questions

433
00:19:38.350 --> 00:19:40.118
about what happened to your husband.

434
00:19:40.152 --> 00:19:43.254
I'm not sure what happened.

435
00:19:43.288 --> 00:19:45.256
We were out on the lake. and I saw

436
00:19:45.290 --> 00:19:47.525
something swimming around us.

437
00:19:47.559 --> 00:19:49.627
We didn't know what it was.

438
00:19:49.661 --> 00:19:52.263
And then it came out of the water.

439
00:19:52.297 --> 00:19:53.698
It was awful.

440
00:19:53.732 --> 00:19:56.634
We were both scared and
Allan grabbed his gun

441
00:19:56.668 --> 00:20:00.571
and shot at it.
and... and it hit the boat

442
00:20:00.606 --> 00:20:02.974
and knocked Allan into the water and...

443
00:20:03.008 --> 00:20:04.642
Did you see anybody else on the water

444
00:20:04.676 --> 00:20:07.111
before you saw what you saw?

445
00:20:07.146 --> 00:20:08.446
No.

446
00:20:08.480 --> 00:20:10.515
Were there any other boats around?

447
00:20:10.549 --> 00:20:14.519
No. we were out there all alone.

448
00:20:14.553 --> 00:20:17.255
I can't believe he's gone.

449
00:20:17.289 --> 00:20:18.856
You rented the boat from there?

450
00:20:18.891 --> 00:20:20.658
Yeah.

451
00:20:20.693 --> 00:20:22.460
All right. thank you for your time.

452
00:20:22.494 --> 00:20:25.530
♪ ♪

453
00:20:25.564 --> 00:20:26.998
I got a theory.

454
00:20:27.032 --> 00:20:29.000
- What?
- She's Wesen.

455
00:20:29.034 --> 00:20:31.402
Kills her husband.
dumps the body overboard.

456
00:20:31.437 --> 00:20:33.338
blasts off a couple rounds.

457
00:20:33.372 --> 00:20:35.306
blames it on the Diamond Lake Monster.

458
00:20:35.341 --> 00:20:37.542
That doesn't explain the photo she took.

459
00:20:37.576 --> 00:20:40.244
Well. somebody's Wesen.

460
00:20:40.279 --> 00:20:42.313
Don't mean to intrude.

461
00:20:42.348 --> 00:20:45.316
I heard what happened.

462
00:20:45.351 --> 00:20:48.252
Just wanted to say that I'm sorry.

463
00:20:48.287 --> 00:20:50.254
Thank you.

464
00:20:53.292 --> 00:20:54.325
♪ ♪

465
00:21:00.798 --> 00:21:03.399
Lake monster sure
isn't hurting business.

466
00:21:05.936 --> 00:21:06.970
Bye. take care.

467
00:21:07.004 --> 00:21:08.538
Hey.

468
00:21:08.572 --> 00:21:11.374
I'm Detective Burkhardt.
this is Detective Griffin.

469
00:21:11.408 --> 00:21:13.510
We need to talk to you.

470
00:21:13.544 --> 00:21:16.546
Um. we're sort of a little busy.

471
00:21:16.580 --> 00:21:18.548
Well. you rented the boat to the victim.

472
00:21:18.582 --> 00:21:21.618
- We just have a few questions.
- Okay. okay. hold on.

473
00:21:21.652 --> 00:21:23.586
Uh. just take over.

474
00:21:23.621 --> 00:21:25.622
Okay.

475
00:21:25.656 --> 00:21:26.623
What's your name?

476
00:21:26.657 --> 00:21:27.824
Wayne Dunbar.

477
00:21:27.858 --> 00:21:29.793
That's my brother. Oliver.

478
00:21:29.827 --> 00:21:31.561
Look. we heard what
happened. and it's terrible.

479
00:21:31.595 --> 00:21:33.129
And we called 911.

480
00:21:33.164 --> 00:21:36.199
Did you or your brother
see anything unusual

481
00:21:36.233 --> 00:21:38.268
on the lake this morning?

482
00:21:38.302 --> 00:21:40.770
Nothing out of the ordinary.

483
00:21:40.805 --> 00:21:42.739
Well. the Eigers took
the boat out about 7:30.

484
00:21:42.773 --> 00:21:46.042
About an hour later. we heard gunshots.

485
00:21:46.076 --> 00:21:47.644
then we heard her screaming.

486
00:21:47.678 --> 00:21:51.281
And we ran down to the water. called 911.

487
00:21:52.562 --> 00:21:54.596
Our first thought was she shot her husband.

488
00:21:54.631 --> 00:21:59.234
So you don't believe
in this lake monster?

489
00:21:59.269 --> 00:22:00.269
Well. we do sell a few items

490
00:22:00.303 --> 00:22:02.037
that suggests that it does exist.

491
00:22:02.072 --> 00:22:03.906
But have I ever seen it? No.

492
00:22:03.940 --> 00:22:06.141
You have a pretty brisk business here.

493
00:22:06.176 --> 00:22:08.477
A lot of gawkers showed
up after the attack.

494
00:22:08.511 --> 00:22:11.046
folks looking to get a
glimpse of the monster.

495
00:22:11.081 --> 00:22:14.316
It's pretty macabre. but
we appreciate the traffic.

496
00:22:14.351 --> 00:22:16.485
How long have you owned the business?

497
00:22:17.854 --> 00:22:19.555
Parents opened it about 50 years ago.

498
00:22:19.589 --> 00:22:21.223
Me and my brother took
over about five years ago

499
00:22:21.257 --> 00:22:22.524
after they passed away.

500
00:22:22.559 --> 00:22:25.628
Your parents ever see the monster?

501
00:22:25.662 --> 00:22:28.831
Oh. my dad swore that he did. Twice.

502
00:22:28.865 --> 00:22:32.468
Yeah. he's the one that started
the whole hat and T-shirt thing.

503
00:22:32.502 --> 00:22:35.437
This is a picture that
he took of it right here.

504
00:22:35.472 --> 00:22:37.840
All my life. I wanted to see this thing.

505
00:22:37.874 --> 00:22:40.009
Oh. sorry.

506
00:22:41.578 --> 00:22:43.979
Oliver!

507
00:22:44.014 --> 00:22:47.516
Excuse me. I got to help my brother.

508
00:22:50.487 --> 00:22:52.921
♪ ♪

509
00:22:53.765 --> 00:22:54.798
Brother's Wesen.

510
00:22:54.833 --> 00:22:55.966
What?

511
00:22:56.000 --> 00:22:57.568
The one who dropped the mug.

512
00:22:57.602 --> 00:22:59.236
He woged when he bent over to pick it up.

513
00:22:59.270 --> 00:23:00.604
Look anything like the lake monster?

514
00:23:00.637 --> 00:23:02.004
No.

515
00:23:02.039 --> 00:23:03.806
I think he's a Luisant-Pêcheur.

516
00:23:03.841 --> 00:23:05.475
looks sort of like an Eisbiber.

517
00:23:05.509 --> 00:23:07.176
- You think they're involved?
- I don't know.

518
00:23:07.211 --> 00:23:08.945
I mean. they sure are benefitting from it.

519
00:23:08.979 --> 00:23:11.447
Better check them out.

520
00:23:11.482 --> 00:23:13.382
<i>The turmeric should
help with your arthritis.</i>

521
00:23:13.417 --> 00:23:15.451
If it doesn't make a difference.
you can bring it back.

522
00:23:15.486 --> 00:23:16.819
- I'll try it.
- Great.

523
00:23:16.854 --> 00:23:19.622
That'll be $17.25. Let
me get you some change.

524
00:23:22.192 --> 00:23:24.093
Okay.

525
00:23:24.127 --> 00:23:25.761
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

526
00:23:25.795 --> 00:23:27.930
♪ ♪

527
00:23:30.467 --> 00:23:34.703
♪ ♪

528
00:23:34.738 --> 00:23:36.238
Hey.

529
00:23:36.273 --> 00:23:38.874
Oh. my God. Trubel!

530
00:23:38.909 --> 00:23:40.175
Oh!
Oof!

531
00:23:40.210 --> 00:23:41.977
- Nick told us you were back.
- Yeah.

532
00:23:42.012 --> 00:23:44.213
Sorry. got to make this a group hug.

533
00:23:45.815 --> 00:23:47.483
How are you?

534
00:23:47.517 --> 00:23:48.784
Pretty good.

535
00:23:48.818 --> 00:23:50.252
How are you guys? I missed you.

536
00:23:50.287 --> 00:23:52.288
We're just glad you're okay.

537
00:23:52.322 --> 00:23:54.390
So you got a motorcycle.

538
00:23:54.424 --> 00:23:57.593
I did. Look.

539
00:23:57.627 --> 00:23:59.929
I need to talk to you guys about something.

540
00:24:03.533 --> 00:24:05.734
Oh. that kind of talk.

541
00:24:05.769 --> 00:24:08.370
You guys know about Black Claw. right?

542
00:24:08.405 --> 00:24:11.607
We do.

543
00:24:11.641 --> 00:24:14.577
There's a lot more you need to know.

544
00:24:15.449 --> 00:24:17.183
<i>Neither of the Dunbar
brothers has a record.</i>

545
00:24:17.217 --> 00:24:19.218
Well. they're pretty deep in debt.

546
00:24:19.253 --> 00:24:20.620
Have some trouble with the IRS.

547
00:24:20.654 --> 00:24:23.656
Owe some taxes. a lien on the property.

548
00:24:23.691 --> 00:24:25.592
Good thing that monster
showed up when he did.

549
00:24:25.627 --> 00:24:28.862
But they couldn't have done it.

550
00:24:28.897 --> 00:24:33.167
Whatever that is. it's
not what the brothers are.

551
00:24:33.201 --> 00:24:35.669
Maybe it was a Wesen for hire.

552
00:24:35.703 --> 00:24:37.237
We need to figure out what kind of Wesen

553
00:24:37.272 --> 00:24:39.706
we're dealing with.

554
00:24:42.243 --> 00:24:44.044
9 grand in one day.

555
00:24:44.078 --> 00:24:45.446
That's got to be a record. right?

556
00:24:45.480 --> 00:24:46.814
Yeah. it's a record.

557
00:24:46.848 --> 00:24:48.315
I mean. we've never sold out before.

558
00:24:48.349 --> 00:24:50.884
Everything's gone...
Hats. mugs. T-shirts.

559
00:24:50.919 --> 00:24:52.653
Even the triple extra-large ones.

560
00:24:52.687 --> 00:24:54.788
I'm bursting with joy.

561
00:24:54.823 --> 00:24:57.257
- That's blood money. Wayne.
- Oh. come on.

562
00:24:57.292 --> 00:24:59.126
Dad would be proud.
That we got a man killed?

563
00:24:59.160 --> 00:25:00.627
It wasn't our fault.

564
00:25:00.662 --> 00:25:01.929
I just don't think this is right.

565
00:25:01.963 --> 00:25:03.397
Then stop thinking.

566
00:25:03.431 --> 00:25:05.365
You know. Mom and Dad worked their fingers

567
00:25:05.400 --> 00:25:07.434
to the bone for this place.

568
00:25:07.469 --> 00:25:09.002
If it was up to you.
we'd be out on the street.

569
00:25:09.037 --> 00:25:10.671
Yeah? Well. what about

570
00:25:10.705 --> 00:25:12.639
if the cops find out about Logan?

571
00:25:12.674 --> 00:25:15.576
How are they gonna find out about Logan?

572
00:25:15.610 --> 00:25:17.111
He was woged.

573
00:25:17.145 --> 00:25:19.746
The witness can't even connect him to it!

574
00:25:19.781 --> 00:25:21.348
You worry too much. brother.

575
00:25:21.382 --> 00:25:24.184
No. the only thing you
got to worry about...

576
00:25:24.219 --> 00:25:26.820
is restocking these shelves.

577
00:25:26.855 --> 00:25:29.156
Where are you going?

578
00:25:29.190 --> 00:25:32.192
Laughing all the way to the bank.

579
00:25:32.227 --> 00:25:36.030
<i>♪ Through all the
books you wish to read ♪</i>

580
00:25:36.064 --> 00:25:37.564
- Bring him another.
- You got it.

581
00:25:37.599 --> 00:25:38.899
And me too.

582
00:25:38.933 --> 00:25:42.269
<i>♪ Want to know ♪</i>

583
00:25:42.303 --> 00:25:43.270
What do you want?

584
00:25:43.304 --> 00:25:48.242
I want you... to do it again.

585
00:25:48.276 --> 00:25:50.511
Tonight.

586
00:25:50.545 --> 00:25:52.279
Wait. You remember?

587
00:25:52.313 --> 00:25:54.715
No. come on.

588
00:25:54.749 --> 00:25:57.651
Do you want to come swim with me?

589
00:25:57.685 --> 00:25:59.153
Oh. my gosh.

590
00:26:02.157 --> 00:26:04.324
♪ ♪

591
00:26:04.359 --> 00:26:05.859
We should ask him.

592
00:26:07.862 --> 00:26:15.869
♪ ♪

593
00:26:27.159 --> 00:26:28.559
Swim to me.

594
00:26:28.593 --> 00:26:30.895
No way.

595
00:26:30.929 --> 00:26:32.897
Are you afraid of the lake monster?

596
00:26:32.931 --> 00:26:34.265
No. I'm not.

597
00:26:34.299 --> 00:26:35.700
Yeah. you are.

598
00:26:35.734 --> 00:26:37.601
I dare you.

599
00:26:37.636 --> 00:26:39.604
What. don't you want to be alone with me?

600
00:26:39.638 --> 00:26:42.106
Then get your butt out here.

601
00:26:42.140 --> 00:26:44.609
♪ ♪

602
00:26:47.646 --> 00:26:49.013
There's something in the water.

603
00:26:49.047 --> 00:26:50.848
Too late. I'm coming to get you.

604
00:26:50.882 --> 00:26:53.618
No. no! No. no. no. no.

605
00:26:53.652 --> 00:26:56.487
♪ ♪

606
00:26:56.521 --> 00:26:57.822
I'm not kidding. Kevin!
What?

607
00:26:57.856 --> 00:26:59.257
Are you afraid the lake
monster's gonna get you?

608
00:26:59.291 --> 00:27:00.691
Oh. my God! It's right in front of you!

609
00:27:00.726 --> 00:27:02.260
Come on in. The water's great.

610
00:27:02.294 --> 00:27:06.931
♪ ♪

611
00:27:06.965 --> 00:27:08.933
Get out of the water!

612
00:27:08.967 --> 00:27:10.735
Kevin. I'm serious!

613
00:27:10.769 --> 00:27:12.336
Kevin! Come on. please.

614
00:27:12.371 --> 00:27:16.040
Come here! Swim! Now!

615
00:27:16.074 --> 00:27:17.575
No!

616
00:27:27.590 --> 00:27:29.491
Rosalee's downstairs.

617
00:27:29.525 --> 00:27:31.926
We think we found what you're looking for.

618
00:27:33.162 --> 00:27:36.031
We think it's a Wasser Zahne.

619
00:27:36.065 --> 00:27:39.267
It's like a Skalengecky
water-loving Wesen.

620
00:27:39.301 --> 00:27:41.102
Did you see
it face-to-face?

621
00:27:41.137 --> 00:27:43.505
- No. but we did see a lot of T
- shirts and hats.

622
00:27:43.539 --> 00:27:45.440
- I got a couple Luisant
- Pêcheur brothers

623
00:27:45.474 --> 00:27:47.108
who might be working with a Wasser Zahne.

624
00:27:47.143 --> 00:27:48.343
Killed a boater out on the lake.

625
00:27:48.377 --> 00:27:49.778
Yeah. we saw the news.

626
00:27:49.812 --> 00:27:51.346
Looks like someone's rebooting the old

627
00:27:51.380 --> 00:27:52.714
Diamond Lake Monster legend.

628
00:27:52.748 --> 00:27:55.717
And whoever he is.
that's probably our killer.

629
00:27:58.621 --> 00:28:00.822
Nick. when you
went to see Juliette...

630
00:28:00.856 --> 00:28:02.390
Eve.

631
00:28:02.425 --> 00:28:03.858
Eve? What?

632
00:28:03.893 --> 00:28:06.795
That's what she calls herself now.

633
00:28:06.829 --> 00:28:10.198
Or it's what they call
her. I'm not really sure.

634
00:28:10.232 --> 00:28:13.668
Okay.

635
00:28:13.703 --> 00:28:15.704
Did you guys have a
chance to talk this time?

636
00:28:15.738 --> 00:28:17.672
She didn't seem that
interested in talking.

637
00:28:17.707 --> 00:28:19.908
She's not really Juliette.

638
00:28:19.942 --> 00:28:23.211
Whatever they did to
her. she's somebody else.

639
00:28:23.245 --> 00:28:25.847
God. this is terrible... I think.

640
00:28:25.881 --> 00:28:27.215
I mean. if it was the old Juliette.

641
00:28:27.249 --> 00:28:28.750
Not the Juliette that was responsible

642
00:28:28.784 --> 00:28:30.885
for killing your mother
and tried to kill you.

643
00:28:30.920 --> 00:28:33.088
I mean. oh. my God. this so confusing!

644
00:28:33.122 --> 00:28:36.277
I'm just gonna... I'm
gonna stop talking.

645
00:28:36.631 --> 00:28:38.832
And also. by the way. Trubel came by.

646
00:28:38.866 --> 00:28:40.333
She wanted to tell us where she's been

647
00:28:40.368 --> 00:28:41.901
and what she's been doing and she told us

648
00:28:41.936 --> 00:28:44.304
about these people that she's working for.

649
00:28:44.338 --> 00:28:46.606
She said they'd be contacting us.

650
00:28:46.641 --> 00:28:48.074
Are you going to help them?

651
00:28:48.109 --> 00:28:49.809
I don't know yet.

652
00:28:49.844 --> 00:28:52.112
Yeah. we're feeling a
little tentative ourselves.

653
00:28:52.146 --> 00:28:54.147
I think whatever we decide.

654
00:28:54.181 --> 00:28:56.850
we all decide the same thing.

655
00:28:56.884 --> 00:28:59.552
We are in this together.

656
00:28:59.587 --> 00:29:00.987
Yeah.

657
00:29:02.344 --> 00:29:03.470
This city deserves safe streets.

658
00:29:04.028 --> 00:29:06.005
and Andrew Dixon is committed
to supporting the hardworking

659
00:29:06.463 --> 00:29:09.332
police officers that keep
our neighborhoods secure.

660
00:29:09.366 --> 00:29:13.336
That's why I'm here to
endorse Andrew Dixon for Mayor.

661
00:29:15.439 --> 00:29:16.973
How's that?

662
00:29:17.007 --> 00:29:18.374
Can I make a suggestion?

663
00:29:18.409 --> 00:29:19.809
Of course.

664
00:29:19.843 --> 00:29:22.779
Instead of saying. "this
city." try saying "we."

665
00:29:22.813 --> 00:29:25.214
"We" deserve safe streets.

666
00:29:25.249 --> 00:29:27.817
It'll be easier for the
voters to get behind you

667
00:29:27.851 --> 00:29:30.753
if you make it clear you're
part of their community.

668
00:29:30.788 --> 00:29:32.121
Okay.

669
00:29:32.156 --> 00:29:34.123
Want to run it again from the top?

670
00:29:34.158 --> 00:29:36.125
- Sure.
- Okay.

671
00:29:41.832 --> 00:29:43.299
♪ ♪

672
00:29:43.334 --> 00:29:46.269
I think we're gonna need to run it

673
00:29:46.303 --> 00:29:48.304
more than once.

674
00:29:48.339 --> 00:29:52.008
♪ ♪

675
00:29:53.212 --> 00:29:54.713
This is getting out of hand.

676
00:29:54.747 --> 00:29:57.215
My lakeshore's turning into a circus.

677
00:29:57.250 --> 00:30:00.619
I've got nuts out on boats
threatening to shoot this thing.

678
00:30:00.653 --> 00:30:02.487
According to the kids
with him. he was swimming

679
00:30:02.522 --> 00:30:04.623
when the thing came right
out of the water. grabbed him.

680
00:30:04.657 --> 00:30:05.991
dragged him under.

681
00:30:06.025 --> 00:30:07.359
I wouldn't let them move the body

682
00:30:07.393 --> 00:30:09.594
until you guys had a chance to see it.

683
00:30:09.629 --> 00:30:12.798
Far as I know. there
are no freshwater sharks.

684
00:30:12.832 --> 00:30:14.232
I'm hoping you guys have some ideas.

685
00:30:14.267 --> 00:30:16.234
'cause I'm at a loss on this one.

686
00:30:16.269 --> 00:30:17.969
Yeah. we're working on something.

687
00:30:18.004 --> 00:30:20.105
<i>Hey. Sheriff. I got
something I want to show you.</i>

688
00:30:23.643 --> 00:30:25.410
We need to squeeze the Dunbar brothers.

689
00:30:25.445 --> 00:30:26.745
How?

690
00:30:26.779 --> 00:30:28.146
Until we know who the Wasser Zahne is.

691
00:30:28.181 --> 00:30:29.381
we can't make a connection.

692
00:30:29.415 --> 00:30:30.849
And we can't take a Wesen to court.

693
00:30:30.883 --> 00:30:32.684
It's the perfect scam.
We need to scare them.

694
00:30:32.719 --> 00:30:34.286
Letting them know you're a Grimm?

695
00:30:34.320 --> 00:30:35.921
Not me.

696
00:30:35.955 --> 00:30:37.789
They need to think they're
getting away with it.

697
00:30:37.824 --> 00:30:45.797
♪ ♪

698
00:30:50.703 --> 00:30:51.903
- There you go.
- Keep the change.

699
00:30:51.938 --> 00:30:53.171
Thank you much.
Thank you.

700
00:30:53.206 --> 00:30:55.107
Come again.
Thanks.

701
00:30:57.643 --> 00:30:59.177
- $24 for a T
- shirt?

702
00:30:59.212 --> 00:31:01.179
15 bucks for a mug?

703
00:31:01.214 --> 00:31:02.547
We need to talk.

704
00:31:02.582 --> 00:31:04.983
Wayne? Wayne!

705
00:31:05.017 --> 00:31:06.451
All right. I'll handle it.

706
00:31:06.486 --> 00:31:08.587
Let's talk in the office.

707
00:31:08.621 --> 00:31:17.029
♪ ♪

708
00:31:17.806 --> 00:31:18.973
Keep going.
Okay.

709
00:31:19.007 --> 00:31:21.542
♪ ♪

710
00:31:21.576 --> 00:31:23.110
You shouldn't be coming around here.

711
00:31:23.145 --> 00:31:24.278
I want half of everything.

712
00:31:24.312 --> 00:31:25.946
Starting yesterday.
What?

713
00:31:25.981 --> 00:31:27.882
You wouldn't have any of
this if it wasn't for me.

714
00:31:27.915 --> 00:31:29.315
I can pay you more.

715
00:31:29.350 --> 00:31:30.917
I can give you a couple hundred right now.

716
00:31:30.951 --> 00:31:32.152
You don't get it.

717
00:31:32.186 --> 00:31:33.787
You've been taking advantage of me.

718
00:31:33.821 --> 00:31:36.689
I do all the work. you
two make all the money.

719
00:31:36.724 --> 00:31:38.591
Well. sure. yeah. we
can work something out.

720
00:31:38.626 --> 00:31:40.693
I'll be back at midnight
to collect the rest.

721
00:31:40.728 --> 00:31:42.228
If I don't get it.

722
00:31:42.263 --> 00:31:44.497
they'll be pulling your
bodies out of the lake.

723
00:31:44.532 --> 00:31:52.439
♪ ♪

724
00:32:00.714 --> 00:32:03.216
What's for dinner?

725
00:32:03.250 --> 00:32:06.886
Not sure.

726
00:32:06.921 --> 00:32:08.855
I don't think he's ready.

727
00:32:08.889 --> 00:32:11.624
- Burkhardt?
- He's still too emotional.

728
00:32:11.659 --> 00:32:13.660
He doesn't understand how
important you are to us...

729
00:32:13.694 --> 00:32:14.961
The way you are now.

730
00:32:14.995 --> 00:32:17.230
Maybe we should've changed my face.

731
00:32:17.264 --> 00:32:19.365
Or do to him what you did to me.

732
00:32:19.400 --> 00:32:20.867
He'll come around

733
00:32:20.901 --> 00:32:24.304
once he realizes what we're up against.

734
00:32:24.338 --> 00:32:30.710
♪ ♪

735
00:32:30.744 --> 00:32:32.612
It's chicken.

736
00:32:33.624 --> 00:32:35.659
I don't like it. I mean.
I don't trust this guy.

737
00:32:35.693 --> 00:32:37.260
He's already killed two people.

738
00:32:37.295 --> 00:32:40.030
And what would make him go
out and kill that poor kid?

739
00:32:40.064 --> 00:32:42.532
I don't know. I mean. he's
obviously out of his mind.

740
00:32:42.567 --> 00:32:44.668
But if he keeps giving us
trouble. we got to deal with it.

741
00:32:44.702 --> 00:32:45.769
Okay. okay.

742
00:32:45.803 --> 00:32:48.872
♪ ♪

743
00:32:48.906 --> 00:32:49.873
Wayne. Wayne. Wayne. no.

744
00:32:49.907 --> 00:32:51.374
No. No!

745
00:32:51.409 --> 00:32:53.243
Listen. here's what we're gonna do.

746
00:32:53.277 --> 00:32:56.546
When he comes back tonight.
he's gonna ask for his money.

747
00:32:56.581 --> 00:32:58.715
And we're gonna give it to him.

748
00:32:58.750 --> 00:33:00.017
And just let him walk out?

749
00:33:00.051 --> 00:33:02.319
No. As soon as you give him the money.

750
00:33:02.353 --> 00:33:03.487
I'm gonna shoot him.

751
00:33:03.521 --> 00:33:04.855
- What?
- It's obvious!

752
00:33:04.889 --> 00:33:06.423
He came here to rob us.

753
00:33:06.457 --> 00:33:11.194
He had the gun. we struggled
over it. and he got shot.

754
00:33:11.229 --> 00:33:14.931
Okay. this whole
thing is out of control.

755
00:33:14.966 --> 00:33:16.566
I think we should just give him the money.

756
00:33:17.568 --> 00:33:20.403
♪ ♪

757
00:33:20.438 --> 00:33:21.938
Sorry. we're closed!

758
00:33:21.973 --> 00:33:24.074
Open the door.

759
00:33:24.108 --> 00:33:27.711
What?

760
00:33:27.745 --> 00:33:29.179
It's a girl.

761
00:33:29.213 --> 00:33:31.648
I'm not here to buy any of your crap.

762
00:33:31.682 --> 00:33:34.151
I'm looking for the Wasser Zahne.

763
00:33:34.185 --> 00:33:35.685
Wayne... -
Open the door!

764
00:33:35.720 --> 00:33:38.555
Okay. okay.

765
00:33:39.676 --> 00:33:41.244
We don't know what you're talking about.

766
00:33:41.278 --> 00:33:42.278
Can you just go away?

767
00:33:42.312 --> 00:33:44.080
Yeah. that's him.

768
00:33:44.114 --> 00:33:45.681
Doesn't look much like that. does he?

769
00:33:45.716 --> 00:33:47.083
Ugh!

770
00:33:47.117 --> 00:33:49.585
These people will just buy anything.

771
00:33:49.620 --> 00:33:51.254
Stop being stupid.

772
00:33:51.288 --> 00:33:52.989
I'm not looking for any Luisant-Pêcheur.

773
00:33:53.023 --> 00:33:55.892
I'm looking for the Wasser Zahne.

774
00:33:55.926 --> 00:33:57.527
There's a contract on his head.

775
00:33:57.561 --> 00:33:58.594
and I'm gonna collect.

776
00:33:58.629 --> 00:34:01.497
Oh. my God. she's a Grimm!

777
00:34:06.003 --> 00:34:07.737
What do you think
you're gonna do with this?

778
00:34:07.771 --> 00:34:10.239
Nothing. I mean. nothing.

779
00:34:10.274 --> 00:34:12.575
Thank God you're here.

780
00:34:12.609 --> 00:34:14.310
The Wasser Zahne's name is Logan Cobb.

781
00:34:14.344 --> 00:34:15.912
He set us up.

782
00:34:15.946 --> 00:34:18.981
He came up with the idea of
bringing back the lake monster.

783
00:34:19.016 --> 00:34:21.951
He attacked those
innocent people on his own.

784
00:34:21.985 --> 00:34:23.786
If we don't sell this
stuff. he's gonna kill us.

785
00:34:23.821 --> 00:34:25.321
We're just patsies selling trinkets.

786
00:34:25.355 --> 00:34:26.989
He's taking all the money!

787
00:34:27.024 --> 00:34:28.858
Where do I find him?

788
00:34:28.892 --> 00:34:31.794
He's coming back here at
midnight to pick up his money.

789
00:34:31.829 --> 00:34:33.830
But if you get rid of
him. we'll give it to you.

790
00:34:33.864 --> 00:34:35.731
And you can still collect on his head.

791
00:34:35.766 --> 00:34:37.834
It's a win-win. He's an old drunk.

792
00:34:37.868 --> 00:34:39.468
Should be no problem for a Grimm.

793
00:34:39.503 --> 00:34:41.437
- Yeah. yeah.
- Midnight. huh?

794
00:34:41.471 --> 00:34:44.073
Yeah. but you got to be here earlier.

795
00:34:44.108 --> 00:34:46.742
♪ ♪

796
00:34:46.777 --> 00:34:48.544
I'll come back at 11:30.

797
00:34:48.579 --> 00:34:52.248
Logan better show.

798
00:34:52.282 --> 00:34:54.250
Huh?

799
00:34:56.053 --> 00:35:02.158
♪ ♪

800
00:35:02.192 --> 00:35:04.160
This is perfect.

801
00:35:04.194 --> 00:35:05.862
Perfect? She's a freaking Grimm!

802
00:35:05.896 --> 00:35:07.930
Yeah. just what we need.

803
00:35:17.091 --> 00:35:25.031
♪ ♪

804
00:35:29.437 --> 00:35:31.605
Well. you were right.

805
00:35:31.639 --> 00:35:34.674
The brothers are working with
a Wasser Zahne named Logan Cobb.

806
00:35:34.709 --> 00:35:36.042
He's been doing the killing.

807
00:35:36.077 --> 00:35:38.011
they've been collecting the profits.

808
00:35:38.045 --> 00:35:40.280
But they claim Logan's
taking all the money.

809
00:35:40.314 --> 00:35:41.882
He's coming back at midnight to collect.

810
00:35:41.916 --> 00:35:42.883
How do you want to do this?

811
00:35:42.917 --> 00:35:44.718
Carefully.

812
00:35:44.752 --> 00:35:47.220
This guy's got a violent record
and lot of assault charges.

813
00:35:47.255 --> 00:35:49.589
And now he's killed two people.

814
00:35:49.624 --> 00:35:51.191
What time do they expect you to be there?

815
00:35:51.225 --> 00:35:53.026
Told them 11:30.

816
00:35:53.060 --> 00:35:55.162
So I guess we'll have to
crash the party a little early.

817
00:35:55.196 --> 00:35:57.364
How far you want me to take this?

818
00:35:57.398 --> 00:35:59.099
Well. he's murdered two people.

819
00:35:59.133 --> 00:36:02.135
And we can't arrest him for it.

820
00:36:02.170 --> 00:36:03.503
That's all I need to know.

821
00:36:03.538 --> 00:36:06.940
<i>♪ Honey ♪</i>

822
00:36:06.974 --> 00:36:08.675
<i>♪ I'm damaged ♪</i>

823
00:36:08.709 --> 00:36:11.378
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

824
00:36:11.412 --> 00:36:14.514
<i>♪ Your halo shines above ♪</i>

825
00:36:14.549 --> 00:36:17.150
<i>♪ Your broken crown ♪</i>

826
00:36:17.185 --> 00:36:19.219
You bring me my money?

827
00:36:19.253 --> 00:36:20.687
No. It's not midnight.

828
00:36:20.722 --> 00:36:22.255
But you come to my place.

829
00:36:22.290 --> 00:36:23.824
I'm not gonna walk around
with that much cash.

830
00:36:23.858 --> 00:36:26.760
Then what are you doing here?

831
00:36:26.794 --> 00:36:28.161
I'm here to warn you.

832
00:36:28.196 --> 00:36:29.329
About what?

833
00:36:29.363 --> 00:36:30.931
My brother. Oliver.

834
00:36:30.965 --> 00:36:33.400
He's gonna double-cross you.

835
00:36:33.434 --> 00:36:34.668
What?

836
00:36:34.702 --> 00:36:36.403
He said he wanted to keep your share.

837
00:36:36.437 --> 00:36:41.007
so he hired somebody to kill
you when you show up tonight.

838
00:36:41.042 --> 00:36:43.210
That little bastard.

839
00:36:43.244 --> 00:36:45.278
I'll kill him.
No. no. no. no.

840
00:36:45.313 --> 00:36:46.446
I got a plan.

841
00:36:46.481 --> 00:36:48.348
Yeah? What?

842
00:36:48.382 --> 00:36:51.752
You kill Oliver.

843
00:36:51.786 --> 00:36:53.286
You want me to kill your brother?

844
00:36:53.321 --> 00:36:56.256
Oliver never believed
in you. not like I do.

845
00:36:56.290 --> 00:36:58.358
I can't just stand by
after everything you've done

846
00:36:58.393 --> 00:37:00.026
and let him get away with it.

847
00:37:00.061 --> 00:37:03.396
♪ ♪

848
00:37:03.969 --> 00:37:06.203
So what's this plan of yours?

849
00:37:06.238 --> 00:37:08.606
Oliver doesn't expect
you until midnight.

850
00:37:08.640 --> 00:37:10.841
But the person he hired comes at 11:30.

851
00:37:10.876 --> 00:37:13.444
So you come at 11:00.

852
00:37:13.478 --> 00:37:16.681
First. you take care of Oliver.

853
00:37:16.715 --> 00:37:19.517
And then we take care
of his assassin together.

854
00:37:19.551 --> 00:37:21.886
♪ ♪

855
00:37:22.280 --> 00:37:26.216
So who'd Oliver hire to kill me?

856
00:37:26.251 --> 00:37:28.686
Some girl.

857
00:37:28.720 --> 00:37:30.354
A girl?

858
00:37:30.388 --> 00:37:33.123
Yeah. yeah. He thinks
you'd never expect it.

859
00:37:33.158 --> 00:37:35.025
Well. this'll be easy.

860
00:37:35.060 --> 00:37:37.561
♪ ♪

861
00:37:37.595 --> 00:37:40.297
What do we do with the bodies?

862
00:37:40.332 --> 00:37:42.032
We dump them in the lake.

863
00:37:42.067 --> 00:37:45.936
And we blame everything on
the Diamond Lake Monster.

864
00:37:48.406 --> 00:37:49.807
- You mean me.
- No!

865
00:37:49.841 --> 00:37:52.609
Shh. Come on. keep your voice down.

866
00:37:52.644 --> 00:37:55.512
Look. This one.

867
00:37:55.547 --> 00:37:57.548
Oh. yeah. that one.

868
00:38:05.624 --> 00:38:10.928
♪ ♪

869
00:38:10.962 --> 00:38:14.398
I see Logan.

870
00:38:14.432 --> 00:38:16.267
I guess he couldn't wait till midnight.

871
00:38:16.301 --> 00:38:17.835
Something else is going on here.

872
00:38:17.869 --> 00:38:20.671
Could be he doesn't trust them.

873
00:38:20.705 --> 00:38:24.141
- You ready?
- Yeah.

874
00:38:25.155 --> 00:38:27.123
What if she's late. okay?

875
00:38:27.157 --> 00:38:29.525
What if she shows up after he does?

876
00:38:29.560 --> 00:38:32.161
What if she doesn't show up at all?

877
00:38:32.196 --> 00:38:33.730
Who?

878
00:38:33.765 --> 00:38:35.966
- Who what?
- Who you were talking about.

879
00:38:36.001 --> 00:38:37.635
Oh. uh... no.

880
00:38:37.669 --> 00:38:39.703
That was something else altogether.

881
00:38:39.738 --> 00:38:41.605
Hey. look at all the money we got for you.

882
00:38:41.640 --> 00:38:44.008
I know all about your plan.

883
00:38:44.042 --> 00:38:45.776
Plan? Uh. what plan?

884
00:38:45.810 --> 00:38:47.211
- To backstab me.
- What?

885
00:38:47.245 --> 00:38:48.979
And take my share.

886
00:38:49.014 --> 00:38:51.148
Hey. hey. hey. I don't know
what you're talking about.

887
00:38:51.183 --> 00:38:54.652
The little girl you hired to kill me.

888
00:38:54.686 --> 00:38:57.054
I didn't hire a little girl to kill you.

889
00:38:57.088 --> 00:38:59.189
Well. that's not what your brother said.

890
00:38:59.224 --> 00:39:00.858
What?

891
00:39:00.892 --> 00:39:02.293
I told him the truth. Oliver.

892
00:39:02.327 --> 00:39:05.996
I had to.
What truth is that. Wayne?

893
00:39:06.031 --> 00:39:07.631
I couldn't let you betray him.

894
00:39:07.666 --> 00:39:09.867
Betray Logan? I-I
didn't betray Lo...

895
00:39:09.901 --> 00:39:11.068
I didn't
betray Lo...

896
00:39:11.102 --> 00:39:13.070
No!

897
00:39:13.104 --> 00:39:14.538
Okay. Logan. no.

898
00:39:14.572 --> 00:39:16.407
I didn't... I
didn't do anything.

899
00:39:16.441 --> 00:39:18.609
- You're gonna taste good.
- No. no. no!

900
00:39:18.643 --> 00:39:21.011
Wayne. tell him! No! Wayne!

901
00:39:21.046 --> 00:39:23.080
Wayne! Wayne!
Hey!

902
00:39:23.114 --> 00:39:26.717
♪ ♪

903
00:39:26.751 --> 00:39:27.952
You're early.

904
00:39:27.986 --> 00:39:29.887
♪ ♪

905
00:39:29.921 --> 00:39:33.257
So you're the little
girl he hired to kill me?

906
00:39:33.291 --> 00:39:35.426
I didn't hire her. Wayne did!

907
00:39:35.460 --> 00:39:36.961
Okay? Wayne did everything!

908
00:39:36.995 --> 00:39:38.996
I didn't even want to do any of this.

909
00:39:39.030 --> 00:39:40.965
Whatever.

910
00:39:45.770 --> 00:39:47.905
You didn't tell me she was a Grimm.

911
00:39:47.939 --> 00:39:49.473
Oops.

912
00:39:54.512 --> 00:40:00.584
♪ ♪

913
00:40:03.088 --> 00:40:10.995
♪ ♪

914
00:40:12.550 --> 00:40:15.519
Wow!

915
00:40:15.553 --> 00:40:18.388
You're really good.

916
00:40:18.423 --> 00:40:21.258
Here you go.

917
00:40:21.291 --> 00:40:24.326
I'll double it if you kill my brother.

918
00:40:24.361 --> 00:40:26.061
Aw. come on. Wayne!

919
00:40:26.096 --> 00:40:27.563
The killing's over.

920
00:40:27.597 --> 00:40:29.064
Yeah. yeah. yeah. We saw it all.

921
00:40:29.099 --> 00:40:30.332
She killed him.

922
00:40:30.367 --> 00:40:31.801
Didn't really have a choice.

923
00:40:31.835 --> 00:40:33.703
He killed two people.
We couldn't arrest him.

924
00:40:33.737 --> 00:40:34.970
Yeah. I guess
you should know...

925
00:40:35.005 --> 00:40:37.807
He's a Grimm just like her.

926
00:40:39.309 --> 00:40:42.745
♪ ♪

927
00:40:43.780 --> 00:40:45.281
It's locked!

928
00:40:45.315 --> 00:40:46.715
He's just gonna go out the back door.

929
00:40:46.750 --> 00:40:48.350
You should go around.

930
00:40:48.385 --> 00:40:50.152
Stay with him.

931
00:40:50.187 --> 00:40:58.060
♪ ♪

932
00:40:59.129 --> 00:41:07.770
♪ ♪

933
00:41:07.804 --> 00:41:09.472
There's no way I'm
going in there after him.

934
00:41:09.506 --> 00:41:11.307
He's got to come out sooner or later.

935
00:41:11.341 --> 00:41:12.842
<i>- I see him!
- Yeah. it's right there!</i>

936
00:41:12.876 --> 00:41:14.543
<i>- Do I see him yet?
- It's the monster!</i>

937
00:41:17.547 --> 00:41:22.184
♪ ♪

938
00:41:22.219 --> 00:41:24.053
How are we gonna explain this one?

939
00:41:29.626 --> 00:41:31.694
Why was this idiot
swimming in the lake at night

940
00:41:31.728 --> 00:41:33.863
with all that's going on?

941
00:41:33.897 --> 00:41:37.033
No wonder he got himself shot.

942
00:41:37.067 --> 00:41:40.002
Maybe he wanted to make
people think he was the monster.

943
00:41:40.036 --> 00:41:42.938
Drum up a little business for the shop?

944
00:41:42.973 --> 00:41:45.408
Maybe that's what he and his
brother were doing all along.

945
00:41:45.442 --> 00:41:48.544
Yeah. Maybe.

946
00:41:48.578 --> 00:41:50.346
But how'd this local
drunk wind up in the water

947
00:41:50.380 --> 00:41:51.380
with a broken neck?

948
00:41:51.415 --> 00:41:53.149
I don't know.

949
00:41:53.689 --> 00:41:58.560
I'm starting to think this
Diamond Lake Monster is real.

950
00:41:58.594 --> 00:42:00.695
Is he serious?

951
00:42:00.729 --> 00:42:03.932
You never know.

952
00:42:03.966 --> 00:42:05.633
Guess it's better
to believe in a monster

953
00:42:05.668 --> 00:42:07.035
than know the truth.

954
00:42:07.069 --> 00:42:08.836
Yeah. 'cause you can
always convince yourself

955
00:42:08.871 --> 00:42:10.371
a monster's not real.

956
00:42:10.406 --> 00:42:13.808
Reality is definitely
not what it used to be.

957
00:42:16.812 --> 00:42:19.380
